summary: This is an FBI evidence chain of custody form (FD-1004) documenting the handling of three phone message books seized from Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach, FL residence. The form tracks the transfer of evidence between law enforcement personnel, primarily from the Miami field office, and shows the items were stored in a Bronx warehouse.

events.title: Evidence Collection from Epstein Residence
events.description: Three phone message books were collected as evidence from Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach, FL residence.

keyFacts: Evidence (three phone message books) was collected from Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach, FL residence on August 28, 2006.
The evidence was handled by the FBI's Miami field office and ultimately stored in a Bronx warehouse under evidence barcode E712&493.
The document is a standard FBI chain of custody form (FD-1004), indicating formal evidence handling procedures were followed.
Signatures on the form are illegible, preventing identification of the specific law enforcement personnel involved in the evidence transfers.
